  \n                \n    \n    \n\n    \n    \n\n                \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n            \n\n            \n                \n            \n\n            \n                \n                    \n                \n                \n                \u003cdiv\u003e\n                    \n                        \u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eAddendum to: \u003ci\u003eNature\u003c/i\u003e \u003ca href=\"https://doi.org/10.1038/nature12318\"\u003ehttps://doi.org/10.1038/nature12318\u003c/a\u003e Published online 12 June 2013\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe Editors would like to alert the readers that concerns have been raised regarding the data presented in Supplementary Figs. 6 and 7:\u003c/p\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n            \u003cli\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eThe flow cytometry plots in Supplementary Fig. 6a appear to have repetitive data point patterns;\u003c/p\u003e\n            \u003c/li\u003e\n            \u003cli\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eThe 53BP1 and Flag lanes 3–5 in Supplementary Fig. 7b appear highly similar (flipped horizontally).\u003c/p\u003e\n            \u003c/li\u003e\n          \u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eAlthough the affected figures do not alter the results or conclusions of the article, readers are advised to interpret these results with caution. The first and corresponding authors are in the process of re-doing these experiments, the results of which will be reported elsewhere.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eAlexandre Orthwein has not responded to any correspondence about this Editorial Expression of Concern. All other authors agree to this Editorial Expression of Concern.\u003c/p\u003e\n                    \n                \u003c/div\u003e\n            \n\n            \u003cdiv\u003e\n                \u003cdiv id=\"author-information-section\" aria-labelledby=\"author-information\" data-title=\"Author information\"\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"author-informa